reviews: Boutique hotel with amazing fabulous decor. Very friendly staff. Lobby and room very clean. We enjoyed complimentary lemonade and water in our room and the very comfortable beds. Basic but decent breakfast, great location. Would stay again. Would recommend.

Found last minute via Booking.com for my family.
Absolutely fantastic clean/modern room and a comfy bed where we had a great night's sleep. Just what was needed after driving from the UK and lots of walking. Nice little surprise with the drinks and mini fridge. Very good location with a variety of restaurants, 20 mins walk to the Seine through the town

Very comfortable and clean hotel. Friendly and helpful staff at reception. Close to Gare du Nord (arrival of the Eurostar) and conveniently located for touristic attractions. Really enjoyed the hotel. A number of vegan cafes nearby.

The room was Always clean and very comfortable. The staff was very friendly. The breakfast was really good. We could do most of sightseeing by foot. But metro station was also nearby. The price was okay (for Paris)

The hotel exceeded my expectations, has got some character, the room was clean and the bed was comfortable. I was happy with my choice! Also, since I like to walk, I was able to get on foot to all the places (St Germain, Marais, Champs Elysees), a bonus point for not needing metro :)

Disgust of a hotel, the service is simply horrible, they don't care about their customers, they steal your money and don't give anything in return
I call the hotel, at the reception they hang up, they don't care about anything, the main thing is that they got their money
Not getting to their hotel at all

complete and varied breakfast, very good sleep quality, this hotel is easily found, not very far away from the subway, quiet place, helpful staff, good value for money, well-heated rooms, this is my third stay and I enjoyed it.

We got an upgrade to a bigger room with balcony and a bathroom with bath and shower. The bed was soo big. The room was excellent and beautiful.

The staff was very friendly. It was possible to leave the baggage in a locked room.

Only the breakfast was not so good for us. It was okay, but don't expect a too big variety of food. Also, it was little bit loud in the night when people talk or call loudly on the floor.

Hotel Aida Opera was lovely. The staff was very personable and helpful...My every need was met with a smile and in a competent manner. The hotel was clean and brightly decorated. It was also a good value! Highly recommend!

Excellent location. Excellent breakfast, buffet.Even fresh fruit, soya milk and deserts .Excellent beds. We had a quiet and big room on the first floor. Lots of restaurants in the neighbourhood. 10 minutes walk to metro station and close to Galeries Lafayette.

The windows are not isolated, to much noise from the street.
The heating always runs on full power, the only possibility of regulation was by air condition. This is really not sustainable.
To much stress in the breakfast room, and very uninspired breakfast.

Clean hotel and room.
Bad behavior from the night receptionist. He was extremely ironic, rude all the night we stayed. We felt uncomfortable due to his rudeness. He was speaking about us in French o another guy and he was laughing (we were Greek and he thought that we dont understand anything). So insolent

good location, room size and cleaniness - the art decor is a bit funky and not for everyone's taste - selection of breakfast should be better as it is not up to the expectation for the type of hotel and price range

We've stayed there before, and have been generally good with it. After three stays, I think I'm tired of the neo-graffitti art in the hallways. Breakfast is OK, with good croissants, but it would be nice to have some cold-cuts. Often a line for coffee, and they keep the 2nd machine shut-off. Lots of hotels in the area, so may try something new next, and since this is spendy, I'd shop around a bit, but could come back.

nice hotel :) very nice staff and very welcoming
the breakfast was good the gym was nice although would be nice if there would be some weights there
Also the vending machine accepts cash only :/

thank you verymuch

I was travelling with a friend and we had a very nice and spacious twin room with a balcony. Lovely.
Breakfast was decent with fresh baguette and pastries.
There are coffee and tea making facilities near the reception.
The hotel is within walking distance of the Gare de l'Est and close to underground station.

We were a family of 12, including 6 children. The staff was very helpful in accommodating all our needs, especially since it was the Christmas week which, of course, is very busy.
The location was excellent for our needs and we completely enjoyed our stay.
Breakfast is good but we felt it was over-priced, Otherwise, we highly recommend the hotel.

My family & I stayed here during our visit to Paris. I loved the tucked location & the fact that it was easily able to get to the subway. The staff was the best part! They were so accommodating, friendly & welcoming! Thank yous!

Overall a decent hotel to stay in Paris. Rooms are relatively new and well furnished, staff is very friendly and helpful, hotel was also very accommodating and allowed early check-in request. Only downside is that the rooms are a bit tight on space, once we have our luggage laid out, there is little space left.

It's a nice place to stay with attentive stuff (they gave us a bottle of wine for the birthday), with heated floors, large room then you can expect for Paris.
They offer breakfast and have a hot drinks station that is always open.

I was in Paris for a trade show and the metro has a good connection to Porte de Versailles. The hotel is located very near to Grandes Boulevards station and there are many restaurants nearby.
The hotel has recently been completely modernised and the rooms are well designed. I had a small problem locating the TV, which is hidden inside a mirror, but I found it eventually. There is plenty of storage space and a desk. The bathroom is well equipped, with a shaving mirror and a good shower.
I would certainly return, if I am in Paris again.

Staff pleasant and helpful. Several metro lines close by and the major department stores are a short walk away. Rooms have been refurbished and modernised. Our room was compact but could do with drawers or shelves for clothes although there is a rail with hangers. The breakfast is kosher, which suited us

Excellent hotel. Close to synagogues and kosher restaurants. Close to the metro. Large rooms. Great service.Excellent hotel. Close to synagogues and kosher restaurants. We got the room at 15:00 close to 10 minutes to the metro. Large rooms. Great service. 15 minutes walking distance from Lafayette Galleries. There is a kosher grocery store. Suitable for a couple with 2 children.

Excellent room with comfortable beds, lovely, large new bathroom, balcony. Very good kosher breakfast, friendly, helpful staff, good location. I was traveling with two teen-aged girls, and we all had an amazing time. A really nice, clean friendly, comfortable hotel.

The hotel was very good, but I was with my father and the toilet does not give two much privacy if youre not partners with the other person on the room.
We asked for two single beds and they were put together as if s double bed

The Aida has made many changes since the pandemic -- all for the worse. The new decor is horrific and unwelcoming, the staff are young, rude, and inexperienced -- it is frankly heartbreaking that my family and I will never stay here again.

We booked this hotel thinking it was an easy walk from Gare du Nord and close enough to the main tourist sites. While we made it work it is important to note that this requires more walking than you'd think. That's nothing against the hotel, however. The rooms were clean but small (which is to be expected in Paris). We had a lovely street view that was still very quiet. The bathroom was bigger than you might expect and the water always hot and with very good pressure. The bedding was very good as well. Our room had a regular bed and a sofa that folded out into a bunkbed. Breakfast was good but not extensive. There are several restaurants nearby as well as a small market. The staff was extremely friendly.

1 night stay for a party of 6, in two rooms. The family room with bunks was great. Facilities were modern and clean. We were on 1st floor, and there was street noise as expected. Free water and sodas in room was a nice touch.

Had a very pleasant stay at your hotel, the room was quiet and comfortable and the staff were very helpful. Breakfast was tasty and overall it was a very good price, would book up at the hotel the next time that I come to Paris.

We wanted to stay close to Gare du Nord as we had an early train back to the UK and this Hotel certainly ticked that box. Conveniently located in 10th District Close with metro stations close by. Nice clean hotel, with bright decor which my children thought was fun. Staff were friendly enough, and we had no complaints. Plenty of restraunts nearby. We would certainly stay here again.

We would most definitely use this hotel again. A lovely base to enjoy our short break in Paris. It is approximately a 10 to 12 minute walk from Gare de nord. the train station on the RER B line. The metro line is approximately a 5 min walk away.

The location was very good with loads of restaurants and cafes in the neighbourhood, The room was big,, modern and clean. A liitle bit too cold as we could not adjust the AC. Good an well refilled breakfast.

Advantages:
Price per value
Clean
Renovated
Breakfast is nice
Location
Kosher

Disadvantages:
Not all the staff are nice
No cooler
hallways are crowded

Jdheveoshsiwvehwuwjebdiwkwheowheveiwveiwjeveiwijj

We had a really nice experience for our week in Paris. We had a really nice street view room with balcony. The receptionier with mustache is really friendly and helpfull. The rooms are clean. The only inconvenient is that they dont have a kitchen for the morning breakfast, they recive all the food from a food company delivery probably, so if you want an omlette or some beacon is not possible. Also they dont really have meat at breakfast, mostly only fish, bread, vegetables and croissants. Its becaming repetitive if you stay for more than a few days.

We had a very loud room on the first floor. After asking if changing into a quieter room would be possible the receptionist really tried and helped us, even though the hotel was fully booked and on the second day we could move into a nice room much quieter. Great service.

Good place, nice lookig rooms, freindly and helpful staff. Hotel is located nearby major metro stations so it was easy to travel arround whole Paris. Pleanty of restaurants nearby! I reccomend it to anyone who consider visiting Paris with family

We loved the location of this hotel and it was very clean.
Check in was easy, there is a lift if you need it.
The rooms are small but I think compared to other hotel in Paris this is a good price.
Id stay again

Problem with the air conditioning in one of the bedrooms and no one in the hotel solved. Poor engkish speeking in the frontdesk.
We asked several times to fix or to change us to another room and no answer back. Trully a bad experience and poor cost/bemefit

Very pleasant hotel, Nice neighborhood. Very clean room. Near the metropolitan. Lots of cafes arround. The staff very helpfull and polite. I will came back for sure, and i recomend this pleasant hotel.

Awful service, all about the .
Booked months ago for a twin room, and arrived to the room to find a double - just after the smirking young male hotel receptionist had assured us it was a twin and took payment.
Total rip off merchants. Go elsewhere. They havent got a clue, and relish (smiling while they do it) ripping people off.

The hotel was ok , the room was little bit small , the front desk guys were nice and helpful but the ladies from the kitchen werent polite.
During breakfast they keep warning my 2 year old daughter not to touch the mirror while she was playing dancing in front of it and touched unintentionally.
She did it not only once but kept saying but her job is also cleaning and I dont understand why she got angried with a little child so much!

Keeping it simple. Amazing location. Literally within 15 min walking of the main square. So many cafes and great restaurants and clubs in the area. Always busy and booming. Room are perfect. All the amenities needed. Great showers, heated towel rack and if you get a privilege room with the balcony it's picture perfect. Fitness gym is more than acceptable. If you chose the breakfast option again it's simple but totally satisfying. Rooms are modern but still Parisien. Front desk service also amazing, definitely will be staying here again when back in Paris. Room size for the l
Privilege room is more than enough. This is Paris if you expect 500 square feet then you are in the wrong country. Even NYC isn't like that unless you want to spend $400 a night. Shower is great, small fridge perfect for my wine and drinks and small finger foods. Balcony view is amazing. Looks like a background for your computer. I will be back later this year with no hesitation.
The front desk workers all great and might not be perfect in English but make every effort to satisfy their clients. See y'all in July!

Lovely hotel, great location. Got upgraded to a room with a balcony and highly recommend. Only negative was room wasnt cleaned on the second day & had to walk up 5 flights of stairs on arrival with cases as the lift was being used by staff.

Room a bit small, beds very comfy, excellent shower. Very modern telephone, tv integrated in a large mirror and you can push buttons to indicate DON'T DISTURB or CLEAN THE ROOM. A large safe free of charge at your disposal.

Friendly and helpful staff, clean and tidy rooms with comfortable beds. Good value for money, however only downfall is there was a suprise 100 deposit when we arrived at the hotel we were not informed of.

The hotels reception staff were courteous and helpful.
You can see that a lot of thought was put into the renovation of the hotel.
Within a walking distance to many of Paris attractions.
Folies-Bergre is meters away

The rooms I booked (Privilege) had more space that what we usually get in France for this price . Clenliness was remarkable in al the premisse . Non-stop free coffe and tea at the recpetion is a plus very much appreciated. Staff was kind and helpful

Very nice and clean hotel, the room was very nice and had a big balcony.
Amazing staff very friendly and helpful.
We would definitely come back and recommend to friends.
We had a car so location wasn't an issue for us.

We have stayed here three times before and will stay again on our next trip to Paris. It is in a safe location, a quick uber ride to the busier areas - or a nice walk. The rooms are very clean and cute and the staff is very nice and helpful. The breakfast is nice...however, it would be nice if they changed it up a bit and maybe offered something hot or some meats to go with the cheeses like most European hotels offer. Other than that, it's a great place to stay!!!

We loved this boutique hotel. It is very well located next to Folies Bergere. There is a market nearby, as well as lots of restaurants (including a great poke place) and shops. The room was spacious, quiet and very stylish. The staff was helpful.

What a nice place to stay in Paris! We came bij Thalys, the hotel is only 15 minutes walk from Gare du Nord. A pleasant neigbourhood, a nice room, a very good breakfast, a lot of musea in walking distance. We really enjoyed our stay.

At Hotel Aida Opera Paris, the room had a high price in relation to the quality. During my stay, the shower siphon didnt work properly, it was clogged. Due to it, after my bath, the floor got wet, naturally I tried to dry it.

At my departure, I asked the hotel personnel and room service if everything was in order. Days later, after checking out properly, the hotel accused me of flooding the room, and leaving blankets in the siphon while the shower was running to damage everything. Under these false accusations, they charged me a 1000 euro fine.

The hotel took advantage on the fact that I left my wallet at the room, to oblige the payment of the fine and press the signature of a document assuming responsibility. I was pushed to it since my documents and wallet are vital when travelling. I did not flood the room, only the shower floor got wet. It is a lack of professionalism and respect towards clients to accuse and fine without fundament nor reason.

I do no travel very often in Paris but when I will be I will return to this hotel. I did many in Paris but this is the best of all.
Nothin else to said. Sorry en I have no time to thing about it.


Having a beautiful view, its a great spot close to Opera house. Many cute bars close by. We really enjoyed our stay with a comfy, large bed in a big clean room with very friendly staff. My personal fave was the TV in the mirror. Wed love to come back any time to one of our favorite Cities in the world.

A great hotel! The bed was very comfortable. The staff was friendly and helpful. The location was great. Close to 2 metro lines. There was tea and coffe around the clock. The kosher breakfast was a plus! Would definitely stay there again.

Good location nearby metro.
Good vibe in hotel
Nice and helpfull personel.
By bicycle, foot and boot you see a lot of different things.
Our trip was a very nice one.
Go and visit Paris. It's worth it!!

The hotel is very well located, close to the metro station. Interesting room arrangement, although very small quite pfunctional. A minus for cleanliness. Fridge in the room with dirty door( fungus). Room cleaned only on the fourth day, on explicit request. Unfortunately the bathroom was not cleaned

We met friendly and helpful staff, a clean room, yet not too spacious. Definitely enjoyed the generous presentation of coffee and cookies. There is a safe place for parking bicycles. Very likely to re-visit this central location in vibrant Paris.

Walking distance from Gare du Nore train station where the Eurostar arrives. Located in a great central area with lots of bars and restaurants.
The room was clean with toiletries etc. The breakfast had a good selection. Would stay there again.

A bit of a walk to the Sites, hotel was clean and nicely renovated ..we had a lovely wrap around balcony. A few cafes and shops. close to the hotel. A bit noisy at night...just use white noise. staff was friendly and helpful. We did not eat at the hotel.

Nice hotel, lot of restaurants nearby easy to reach from Gare du Nord by foot, simple but good
Breakfast, friendly personnel.
Room had a good size and modern with smart TV.we certainly stay there again in Paris

Upgraded hotel from last visit. Great location reasonable price. Room clean and comfy great shower. Hotel staff pleasant all amenities close by.
Cheap travel round Paris on metro 16 for ten journeys.

Very nice experience. 20min walk from some attractions and less than 5min from metro. Very nice room and nice staff! Lovely restaurants near by and also a supermarket. We will be definitely go back if we come back to Paris!

This hotel is very nice. It has good beds and modern shower. If you wish they clean your room every day. Our room was very clean and so was the lobby and breakfastroom. From the hotel it is not far to the highlights of Paris.
A pitty was that the french bread and croissants did not seem fresh on our breakfast table.

The room was smaller then on a cruise ship. If you are larger then skinny, you have a problem moving around. The cleaning did come on day 4, even though we asked for that every evening and morning. Really bad. The doors make lots of noise, sounds like slamming all the time and makes it hard to go to sleep.

Cozy, clean, air-conditioned rooms. Friendly and helpful staff. Lovely and safe location with lots of cafes and restaurants. Close proximity to three Metro stations that will take you to anywhere in the city. Perfect place to stay!

This place is very beautiful, the location is absolutely TOP NOTCH! There is airconditioning available on the hotel rooms, this is very nice if you wake up with a hangover. (Something that's very common when in Paris ;) ). So I would recommend this hotel to all my friends.

Hotel Aida Opera was lovely. Great location, clean rooms, friendly and helpful staff.
We stayed 3 nights, will come back again.
Rooms are very modern with comfy bed, full opening windows, towel warmer, and waterfall shower!

Very friendly and helpful staff. The room Was nice, the TV was modern. Breakfadt Was ok, because of Corona you had to take it to your room. For that you had a table for eat your breakfast in bed, very nice idea. We enjoyed our trip :)

Excellent service and confortable room, good location, clam with little noise, clean prmisses. the free coffee, water and snacks is a good idea that should be maintained as encouragement for guests to come back again

There was no breakfast service as I was in France lockdown.
I wanted room service for breakfast.
The room was clean and nice.
It's unpleasant because the hallway smelled of cigarettes.Title your review.

The hotel is nice, designer style, clean, confortable, the staff is kind and attentive, have good installation. Is near to the Opera Garnier (just 5 min walking) and some other interesting places. I will back very soon. Recommended!

Great place to stat. Family room was perfect. Clean room. Nearby subway stations and gare du Nord. 15 min to the walk. Enough restaurants nearby the hotel also supermarkets and bakery. Great hotel to stay a few days in Paris

Hotel is within walking distance of most attractions and the main train stations and the metro ,staff are very accommodating and friendly, hotel itself is very clean and inviting, free tea and coffee for all residents,

Booked the superior double room which was spacious. The room was clean and heated, with a balcony. Breakfast was good, but don't expect to find a variety. Good location as, 15 minutes walk from Gare du Nord and within 5 minutes walk from Metro stations

Top hotel at good and easy to reach location (walking distance from Gare du Nord). The hotel serves a nice breakfast and works with a very friendly staff. Easy to find a nice place for dinner or a drink in this neighbourhood. A place to come back.

The hotel is located in a great place, close enough to all the sites. Nice cafes and bars that are not too touristy (i.e. expensive). I believe it's the people who 'make' a hotel stay great - and Hotel Aida Opera have brilliant staff. They are so welcoming, friendly and helpful. The room was fab and spotless. It is nice and quiet too. I would highly recommend this hotel and will definitely stay there again on my next trip to Paris.

Enjoyed our stay here. Hotel was as expected, easy to get to from Gare De Nord and reasonably close to the Metro. Staff were friendly and continental breakfast was reasonably good. Nothing special but just what we wanted and would happily return here.
Very nice, clean and comfortable hotel with excellent service. ,  ,  ,  . We walked to the center, returned late, the area is safe. Many rastorans and cafe. From the Airport 40-50 Euros by taxi.

OK- time to tell the truth- we came to this place because it provides a kosher breakfast, and we thought that that would be a great way to start our day, and it was. We were quite content and happy with that.

True- it wasnt at all as varied and elaborate and extensive as we know from big resort Israeli hotels, but we were quite happy. After all, it is a small hotel with polite staff.

Yes- other reviewers complained that it was the same thing every morning for breakfast... heck- my wife is the same every morning too, and thats just fine with me.

We mingled with the other guests who came also because of the kosher breakfast.

We have no complaints about the room- functional and fine.

After a few days, we moved to another hotel for the weekend (nope- no kosher breakfast).

Great location and service. We traveled with our family of 6 and were accommodated perfectly. WE got two adjoining rooms, we checked in early. They were ver accommodating. There are a ton of restaurants near the hotel with great food, a pharmacy across the street. We will be back.

Wonderful find of a lovely hotel which is wheelchair accessible. Access via the main entrance which is refreshing. Friendly welcoming reception staff. Light and airy room with gorgeous balcony. Bathroom was very spacious with a great walk in shower.

I have spent good time.
Nice
Clean
Thank you to the staff very welcoming.
Position central of Paris near to everything
After the renovation. It looks much more nice
I hope to come and visit Aida Opera few more times

We took 2 of the bigger rooms - 2 adults in each (room accommodates up to 4). The rooms were comfortable and clean. My bathroom was huge. The staff was very friendly, service was excellent. Had a great experience.

We had a lovely 3 night stay, rooms are very comfortable and modern. The staff were excellent and really helpful. There is only 1 lift and we were on the 6th floor but the lift was always prompt and never had to wait too long. Breakfast was nice however not sure we would have this included in a future stay unless a larger selection was available. The location of the hotel is excellent and was perfect base to see all the sights of Paris.

The location was great and very convenient to the Louvre, the staff were lovely, and the bed was very comfortable. I didn't have the breakfast so I can't review that, but I did enjoy the free snacks in the afternoons. I wasn't expecting to have a balcony so that was a nice bonus. If (when!) I return to Paris I will be sure to stay here again.

A beautiful place to stay, a lovely little balcony in a lovely room, relatively roomy enough for European standards but full of mod con's, such as TV was in the mirror and a direct USB for phone charging. Great lighting and air conditioning, also unusual for Europe. Only slight gripe would be that I prefer tea/coffee facilities in the room but they were available on the ground floor at any time. Lovely friendly, helpful staff. Not as handy to main attractions as we had hoped but only a 15 min walk to Gare de Nord Station & a 10 min walk to the nearest Metro which took us easily to the Arc de Triomphe. We used the Hop On Hop Off buses to get us to all the other attractions but that was about a 45 min walk to get too. But very handy to dining places, markets, laundromats, pharmacies etc. Overall a wonderful stay.

We loved the front desk staff! Rooms were very nice and clean! Great place for a family, they have a couch that turns into a bunk bed! Complimentary snacks mid day! We ubered or walked everywhere. It was a pretty good location.

Very friendly staff, very very clean hotel, effort was certainly put into the decorations, very professional but the breakfast is meagre and I would recommend against taking it. Otherwise I would recommend staying here, we had a very nice stay.

Room & decor were very modern & a great departure from older elaborate or not so modern rooms we stayed in in other countries. Reception folks were very helpful in getting tickets to different things. Many restaurants nearby & market. Wish there was more variety in breakfast food (was exactly the same each of the 7 days we were there).

Rooms are small and clean. In the lobby you would find beverages for guests which is very nice. Stairs are kind old, elevator is typically earopean small.
Breakfast is nice.
The reason I chose it was for the location, and it is close the Laffaye if you like shopping.
Price is acceptable compare to the location, you would not find cheaper ones easily in downtown Paris.

Friendly staff, excellent location, the breakfast is minimal, no hot dishes.
there is tea/coffee area which was nice.
The decoration style is modern, with leftover of original staircase.
Reccomend to book a shuttle back to airport at the reception, it would be cheaper for party of two.

The maintenance engineer left crud matter on the floor instead of clearing it up and then left the door to the room wide open thus allowing anyone access to our belongings. The lock on the WC door needs lubricating.

Very unprofessional management for this hotel, they are looking for your money only. They do not care about the customers. Avoid this hotel this are not decent

I booked hotel rooms in Paris on the Expedia website. The hotel send me massage while I am traveling asking I am attend or not and if I do not replay back within 2 hour they will cancel my request. When I attend to the hotel they mention they try to contact me and they cancel my reservation and I cant refund my money because I dont show up on.

Avoid this hotel this are not decent

Lovely staff, great location, decent room for the price, we were able to walk to most attractions. The only issue was that our first floor room smelt of smoke a few times. I don't know where this was coming from as the hotel has a no smoking policy. It's not the hotel's fault and is my only issue with the entire stay.

Liked the location (near follies Bergeres) so if you like the area and where you can easily go to from here, it's a good choice. I walked everywhere, never even took a tube, taxi or RER anywhere. All is being refurbished, so you can really the effort and the rooms are quite nice already. For a 3 star, this is very adequate albeit in comparison, on average, perhaps price should be lower. Excellent check in, very impressed how fast and diligent (if you tell me who it was i would like to mention her name!). Helpful keeping all the luggage until my train back home, which is again a plus for me: walking distance to Gare du Nord. All in all, very happy.

Stayed at this externally modest 3-star hotel but pleasantly surprised by the modern and efficient interior renovated with artistic flair. Room featured all the mod-cons of a hotel with higher star ratings (family room on the top floor). From check-in to check-out the Reception was friendly helpful and efficient. The location suited our needs well and several Metro options are close by (5-8 minutes walk). A good find and when we return to Paris over the coming months this is likely to be our hotel of choice.

The hotel is lovely and the staff is very friendly and helpful with every request and question. I would recommend you to everyone
The hotel is lovely and the staff is very friendly and helpful with every request and question. I would recommend you to everyone. The breakfast is kosher and very tasty. The hotel rooms are clean and beautifully renovated.

UPDATE: Management tried to twist the fact that they never responded to my email about exchanging my bookings for next trip, and even used the word "politically incorrect" for a personal emergencyPeople, just keep in mind next time you had an emergency and had to change your trip, the hotel will put you into the "not politically correct" category.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Just posting my story here in case anyone else might experience the same situation in the future - I booked a room with them for a few nights stay, unfortunately, had a last-minute personal emergency (with proof) and had to cancel the trip. The hotel management had zero flexibility and refuse to negotiate on any terms and instead went ahead and charged the full amount of my "stay". I suggested paying for the nights already missed and refund/credit the rest part of the stay (it was more than 10 nights) - no, can't do. The hotel couldn't care less that life happens and sometimes people had to change their plans based on reasons that are beyond their control. So my fellow travelers, unless you are fairly certain your trip is going to have no delays, no cancellations, and 200% according to plan, I suggest you look otherwise because the hotel management lacks the very basic respect for customer service.

Excellent friendly, clean, warm, comfortable, all l could ask for. I was visiting Paris for the first time and was thrilled with my choice of Hotel. Very modern.Loved it. Would definetely stay here again.
